race.comment: GETS THE GIRLS (2) is finding the breakthrough elusive, beaten 3.5 lengths into sixth at his latest appearance over 1300m at Northam. Backmarker who gets home hard. This looks the best opportunity he's had for a long time to knock one off. Form good enough, just needs to deliver now. PROVE ME WRONG (5) is a nine-start maiden who finished fourth at her most recent appearance over 1500m at York. Likely to be in the finish in this suitable assignment if he can continue to build into her campaign. I'LL TELL AL (7) was in the firing line on the corner and finished second last start over 1500m at Moora, beaten 1.4 lengths. In the right race and is one of the big hopes. DUCIMAN (3) finished in seventh after being prominent at the bend at his last appearance over 1695m at Bunbury on September 29. Finds the right race and is worth consideration. ADMIRETHEBEAUTY (9) is worth including.
